HEADWORD: Tillodontia
<hw>Til`lo*don"ti*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct group of Mammalia found fossil in
the Eocene formation. The species are related to the carnivores,
ungulates, and rodents. Called also
<altname>Tillodonta</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

